    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.removeAvatar() during an active three-player round.",
      "The fixture advances through Game.onStart() and delayed PrintManager.start(), then calls Game.removeAvatar() for avatar 2.",
      "It proves the leaver is destroyed to present=false/alive=false, emits player:leave, is not added to Game.deaths, and the round continues while avatars 1 and 3 remain alive.",
      "A later forced wall death for avatar 3 ends the round and shows survivor scoring still uses the full avatar collection size."
    ]
  },
